MARYLAND CASUALTY COMPANY, Appellant, v. Ignacio SANABRIA, Jr., Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. November 23, 1929. No. 5710. Dick O. Terrell, of San Antonio, Tex. (Dick O. Terrell and Terrell, Davis, McMillan & Hall, all of San Antonio, Tex., on the brief), for appellant. G. Woodson Morris, of San Antonio, Tex., for appellee.

Before WALKER and BRYAN, Circuit Judges, and DAWKINS, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
